main event: The observer reported seeing a lighted, rectangular-shaped object in the sky while driving home on Route 66 in Chatham, New York on April 25, 1966.
interesting points: The object had a ball-shaped formation in the center and a half-moon-shaped light on the right, separated by dark bands and light beams in an uneven, spike-like arrangement.
The object oscillated back and forth, with the beams emitting tiny, equally bright lights at the ends.
The object moved very little to the north about 75 to 100 yards over the course of the 45-minute observation, from 11:30 PM to 12:15 AM.
The brilliant lights from the object made the brightest stars appear dim in comparison.

The observer decided not to immediately report the sighting to anyone in an official capacity, but waited until the following day, April 27, to send the report to Major Hector Quintanella, Jr. of Project Blue Book.
sighted object: a lighted, rectangular-shaped object with ball-shaped and half-moon-shaped formations
